## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
On this day, I learned the basics of **Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)** in Python and applied it by building a **True/False Quiz Game**.

- The quiz presents a series of True/False questions.
- The user enters an answer (`True`/`False`).
- The program checks the answer and keeps track of the **score**.
- The game continues until all questions are answered.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Concepts Practiced
- Classes & Objects
- Attributes and Methods
- Constructors (`__init__`)
- While loops
- Data management (separating question data from logic)

